cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper proposes a sequence labeling framework with a secondary training objective that improves performance on various natural language processing tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses machine learning techniques, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of general-purpose patterns of semantic and syntactic composition, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The tasks evaluated in the paper include named entity recognition and chunking, which are common in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper could also be relevant to cs.CV (Computer Vision) since it deals with sequence labeling.
